message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. Angiosarcoma is a rare type of cancer that arises from the lining of blood vessels and can occur after radiation therapy or lymph node dissection for breast cancer. Therefore, the history of mastectomy with lymph node dissection is the most likely predisposing factor. The other options are unrelated to the development of angiosarcoma.
